  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Planned Cancer Treatment - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_planned_cancer_treatment">Planned Cancer Treatment</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_planned_activity">PLANNED ACTIVITY</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_planned_cancer_treatment">Planned Cancer Treatment</xref>
 is the proposed treatment(s) agreed at a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_multidisciplinary_team_meeting">Multidisciplinary Team Meeting</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
Note: this may not be the same as later agreed between the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 and the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional">CARE PROFESSIONAL</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
There may be more than one 
              <xref outputclass="attribute"
               keyref="attribute_planned_cancer_treatment_type">PLANNED CANCER TREATMENT TYPE</xref>
 proposed within a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_cancer_care_plan">Cancer Care Plan</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
